{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"264e124c-471d-4b9f-a1bf-0a7909e190d4","content":"CLR activation logs won't help here. They only track **which .NET runtime version gets loaded** by the shim (`mscoree.dll`) — things like runtime selection, version conflicts, and Feature-on-Demand dialogs.\n\nA **NullReferenceException** is an application-level bug (code dereferencing a `null` reference), not a CLR activation issue.\n\n**Better approaches to diagnose your crash:**\n\n1. **Check the stack trace** — it tells you exactly which line hit `null`.\n2. **Enable first-chance exception logging** — attach a debugger or use `dotnet-dump`.\n3. **Review startup code** — look for uninitialized services, missing config values, or DI registration issues.\n\nIf you can share the **exception stack trace** or your **startup code**, I can help pinpoint the bug. Or if you suspect the **wrong .NET runtime is being loaded** (which could *indirectly* cause crashes), I can invoke the CLR activation debugging skill for that.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3c2e576e-0ec9-4dd1-9af6-a3fee0ebab2b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking me to analyze CLR activation logs to diagnose a NullReferenceException in their .NET app. Let me check if there's a relevant skill for this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see \"clr-activation-debugging\" which \"Diagnoses .NET Framework CLR activation issues using CLR activation logs (CLRLoad logs) produced by mscoree.dll.\"\n\nHowever, I need to think about whether this is the right tool. The user has a NullReferenceException, which is typically an application-level bug, not a CLR activation issue. CLR activation logs deal with which runtime version gets loaded, not application exceptions.\n\n\nI should be upfront with the user that CLR activation logs won't actually help here—a NullReferenceException is an application-level error where code is dereferencing a null reference, whereas CLR activation logs only track which .NET runtime was selected and loaded. I should suggest more appropriate approaches instead.","outputTokens":486,"requestId":"980F:1B2DC6:B029F6:CEEB1E:69F4035D"},"id":"78f5caf6-adf1-4099-91d7-f6f1dd0e8fc8","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:35:36.782Z","parentId":"67f027b3-4034-4595-9c96-a0fdc5069258"}
